headline: Michel Duclos, former diplomat: 'Recognizing a Palestinian state is a step toward a peace'
subhead: Michel Duclos examines the possible consequences of the 'New York Declaration,' adopted on September 12 by the United Nations General Assembly, in support of a two-state solution. He argues that the resolution is not an end in itself but an additional step in a long diplomatic process.

headline: Previously unknown Picasso portrait revealed in Paris
subhead: The colorful oil painting, entitled 'Bust of a woman with a flowery hat,' depicts Dora Maar, an artist and Pablo Picasso's muse. It is being put up for auction in Paris, with a reserve price of €8 million.

headline: El Salvador: From 'Surf City' beaches to overflowing prisons, the two sides of the Bukele model
subhead: President Nayib Bukele has propelled El Salvador to the top of the world ranking for incarceration rates, with nearly 1.7% of the population behind bars. At the same time, the Central American state has welcomed 3.5 million tourists, far outpacing Costa Rica.
